# Grounding And Data Safety

- Only return AI answers that can be traced to available datasets and executed queries.
- If data is missing, request missing input instead of inferring.
- Never mix tenant data across retrieval, transformation, or response composition.
- Preserve raw source data and use versioned metadata workflows for edits.
- Include provenance references for critical outputs when available.
